title: Haunted House
overview:
Haunted House
    
        Play Haunted House demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: A medium to high variance slot with a Halloween theme and the potential for big wins in the free spins bonus. With two Stacked Wilds on the reels during base play and in the bonus round and an RTP of 96.14% Haunted House is a slot worth playing.

Haunted House Review.text:
Haunted House is a video slot coming from Habanero. The slot has a spooky appearance which perfectly fits the game theme and comes with a medium to high variance.
Players can score some nice payouts during base play and in the bonus round, but you also have a chance to win one of the three attached random jackpots. Even though the jackpot payouts are not in the millions they can be a pretty nice boost to your balance.

Theme and Visual Details.text:
The game comes with a popular Halloween theme. You will find many other games from other providers with the same theme and you can also find a few other slots with the same name.
The symbols in the slot have a simple design, while the game has an overall dark tone which is to be expected and flows perfectly with the game theme.
The animations which the designers used are not on the top level, but are still good enough to make Haunted House a visually attractive game.

Gameplay.text: The gameplay in the slot is quite fun. This is mainly due to the two Wild symbols in the slot which can help form frequent payouts. They can also land stacked across the reels so players can score a big win in a single spin. Of course the excitement will raise once the bonus round is triggered where even bigger payouts can land on the reels.

media.caption: Gameplay video of Haunted House

Bet size and payouts.text:
The bet size in Haunted House can range anywhere from $0.25 up to a massive $5,000 per spin. This is great news for all high roller players who like to bet big amounts per spin and win even bigger ones in return.
The highest payout in the game comes from landing 5 Scatters on the screen in which case the player will get a hefty payout of 200 times the total stake.
The RTP value in the game is set at 96.14% and the game has a medium to high variance, which goes well with our suggested slot strategies.

media.caption: Paytable of Haunted House slot

Bonus features.text:
The biggest excitement in the slot during base play and in the bonus round comes from the Wild symbols.
The Vampire Wild symbol will replace for all other symbols except for the Scatter and can land on reels 2, 3 and 4 only. It can land stacked across the reels and will also double any payout it substitutes in.
The second Wild symbol in the game is Frankenstein. It can land on all of the reels and will substitute for all other symbols except for the Scatter and the Vampire Wild. It too can land stacked across the reels.
The slot also comes with a free spins bonus round which is triggered when 3, 4 or 5 Haunted House Scatters land anywhere on the reels. The player will need to make picks from the Haunted House Windows and each one can reveal a free spins number or a Ghost symbol.
When two Ghost symbols are revealed the free spins number is tallied up and the bonus round begins. All payouts during the free spins bonus are doubled and the feature can be re-triggered by landing another set of 3 or more Scatters on the screen.
The jackpots in the slot can be won randomly on any spin. A message will appear that the Mini, Minor or Major Jackpot has been won.

media.caption: Frankenstein Wild symbol is stacked on the reels
Game rules of Ghost feature and Jackpot

Conclusion.text:
Haunted House is an interesting Habanero slot which can produce some great payouts. Players can place high bets in the game ranging up to $5,000 per spin and have a chance to win big during base play and in the free spins bonus.
As in all other jackpot slots you also have a chance to win one of the attached progressive jackpots which can be won on any spin.

Baccarat Online Game Review.text:
Baccarat is a variation of the classic casino card game created by games provider Habanero. It's one of two baccarat titles they have released, alongside Baccarat Zero Commission.
You can play Baccarat online for free as part of the range of Baccarat games we have on Casino Guru. Read on to find out about its design, gameplay and special features, as well as info about its basic rules.

media.caption: Win in the Habanero's Baccarat, free to play version

About Habanero.text:
Habanero develops online casino games and software from its base on the island of Malta. Its portfolio consists of a wide range of slots and table games, including the baccarat online games we've mentioned.
The company uses HTML5 technology so that all its games are compatible with mobile devices, and it's regulated by the Malta Gaming Authority (MGA) that is focused on fair gaming and player safety.

How to play baccarat online for free.text:
Playing free baccarat is easy via Casino Guru. To find games like Baccarat by Habanero, just go to our free casino games page and select 'Baccarat' from the 'Game Type' filter. You'll then see a selection of games available to you in your location.
You can then sort these by various filters, including 'Recommended' (we advise you to start with these), 'Recently Added', and 'Highest Return to Player (RTP)'.
When you see one that you like, just click on its play symbol to load the game and start playing for free.

Baccarat Game Design and Graphics.text:
Like with many Habanero games, Baccarat boasts a sharp, slick design with a typical playing table laid out in the form of three racetracks displaying the three options: Player, Banker, and Tie. It uses bright and distinct colours, such as a vivid green for the tabletop, and the chips and cards are clearly marked.
As you play, you'll hear the swift, crisp sounds of chips being moved and cards being dealt, which suit the quick pace of the game.
Beyond the table, though, there's just a black void, which is a shame as it feels like you're playing on a floating rectangle rather than being in a casino. Habanero could improve on this for future releases, perhaps, by adding a dealer figure and surrounding casino items.

Baccarat Gameplay.text:
Once you place your bet, the game is decided instantly, which will appeal to players who like to play quickly.
The game is simple to follow and it's easy to slip into a rhythm once you start playing. This may not be a good thing, however, as you might lost track of how much you're betting if you're playing for real money. Remember to always keep an eye on your balance as you play, not to play too quickly, and to stop immediately if you feel like you're not in control.

All of these give you some form of control over how you play, and are very simple for you to use.

media.caption: Bet limits for the Habanero's free to play Baccarat

Baccarat special features.text:
Baccarat is a game based on simplicity, and focusses on just the standard card game and a basic explanation of the rules. There are no side bets, for example, that some baccarat games allow players to make.
Once nice feature, though, is a useful 'roadmap' at the bottom of the table which shows you your previous bets and who won. This shouldn't be used as any kind of guide to what will happen next, though, with each bet a pure game of chance that's unaffected by past games.

Conclusion.text:
If you're looking for a no-nonsense game of baccarat, then this Habanero's game is for you. It's clear, easy-to-play and doesn't bother you with complicated extras or annoying characters.
That said, you may find that the entertainment wears thin after a while, as the lack of variety makes the gameplay a little repetitive. It's crisp yet unimaginative design may have some players yawning, too.
To summarize, Baccarat by Habanero is a solid, dependable choice for Baccarat fans – just don't expect any surprises!

title: Bubble Bubble 2
overview:
Bubble Bubble 2
    
        Play Bubble Bubble 2 demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Bubble Bubble 2 has simply too high a vig to be worth playing (RTP: 94.5%).

Theme and Storyline.text:
Bubble Bubble 2 is a witch themed slot with plenty of spooky cartoon-style and more than a little sex appeal thrown in.
If one can forgive the title for being a misquote (the line from Shakespeare is "Double, double, toil and trouble / fire burn and cauldron bubble") and for the egregious punning in the symbols ("The Joy of Hex"), then this is a light-hearted Halloween romp anyone might enjoy.
Think Buffy the Vampire Slayer meets Sabrina.

media.alt: Bubble Bubble 2 win with expanding Wild
media.caption: Win with one of the expanding Wild symbols, witch Winni

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are excellent. Well drawn, fun spin on sexy halloween costumes. The non-witch characters are all unique and charming. Each one shows a great deal of character.
The animations are a bit underwhelming, not nearly as exciting as the other visuals might suggest.
The music and soundtrack make up for this somewhat, though not entirely. They add some atmosphere and keep things at the lighter end of spooky.

Gameplay.text:
Bubble Bubble 2 is a five reel slot with three rows. There are 50 win lines.
The three bonus options make for some varied play. But on the whole, this is a pretty straightforward game.
There is no gamble feature.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There are two types of Wild symbols in the base game – Winni, which appears only on reel 1, and Wanda, which appears only on reel 5. These Wilds substitutes for all symbols, including the Scatter symbol, and expand to fill their reel. Wins including a Wild get a x3 multiplier, whereas wins including both Wilds get a x9 multiplier.
Three or more Scatters anywhere on the reel trigger one of three possible bonus features.
The Ultra Bewitched Feature awards 7 free spins in which every spin drops an expanded Wild onto either reel 1 or 5 or both. This happens every single spin.
During the Greater Ghosts Feature, the player is awarded 20 free spins. During the free spins, if the player lands a paying Scatter combo, up to 9 Ghost Wilds are added at random to the reels. These Wilds substitute for all symbols except for the Scatter symbol.
The Wilder Witches Feature is the big kahuna with the potential for enormous wins. In this feature the player is awarded 9 free spins.
During the Free Spins, any witch appearing will cast a spell, turning another reel into all Wilds. If both Witches appear, the middle reel will become Wild, or 33 additional spins will be added to the player's total.
At the end of the Wilder Witches Feature, if the player has won 10-times the player’s bet per spin or less (from the bonus game alone, not counting wins from the triggering spin), they are awarded a bonus prize ranging from 5 to 100-times the bet per spin. If the player has won nothing at all in the bonus feature, they receive 100-times their bet per spin. This is the Realtime Gaming Win-Win Feature.

media.alt: Bubble Bubble 2 win with Ultra Bewitched feature
media.caption: One of the three bonus features

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 94.5%, which is extremely low. Our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.50 up to a maximum of $/£/€12.50 per spin.
The volatility of this game is high, which would make it a good match for our preferred slot machine strategies if the RTP weren’t so terrible.

media.caption: Full paytable for Bubble Bubble slot

Conclusion.text:
Though nice to look at and fun to play, there is very little point booting this game up.
The RTP is so low as to make it far too expensive to play. Even the high volatility can’t make up for that.
We recommend avoiding this one like a haunted house or a black cat.

title: Classic Fruit
overview:
Classic Fruit
    
        Play Classic Fruit demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: A classic 3-reel, 5 payline slot coming from 1x2 Gaming. With a top payout of 200 coins and a low to medium variance Classic Fruit is not a slot which will make you rich in a single spin.

Classic Fruit review.text:
Classic Fruit is a 3-reel classic slot coming from the 1x2 Gaming portfolio. As expected the game has a simple appearance and doesn’t come with any bonus features attached.
In most other classic slots the biggest excitement comes from the strong paytable, but in this game even that is absent since the top payout is set at 200 coins per payline.

Theme and Visual Details.text:
As you have surely guessed by now the slot comes with a fruit theme, which is common to a big number of classic slots.
The visual details are on a low level, but the game has a vibrant choice of colors and a few decent animations which make it reasonably attractive to the eye.

media.caption: Simple win in a simple slot

Gameplay.text: Compared to most other classic slots the gameplay in Classic Fruit is a bit more interesting. This is mainly due to the fact that most of the low paying Fruit symbols award a payout for 2 of a kind wins. Thanks to this there’s always some action on the reels and your balance doesn’t get eaten up too fast.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Bet sizes and payouts.text:
Classic Fruit is a 5 payline slot where players can bet anywhere from $0.05 up to $25 per spin.
The top payout in the game is set at 200 coins for landing a 3 of a kind win with the Red Seven symbol. The game has a low to medium variance and comes with an RTP value of 96.21%.

media.caption: Paytable for highest paying symbols in Classic Fruit slot machine

Bonus features.text:
Unfortunately, like in most other classic slot, Classic Fruit doesn’t have any bonus features. The designers didn’t even add a Wild or Scatter symbol, so everything depends on the payouts of the regular symbols.
Another fact which doesn’t work in favor of the game is that the symbols can’t land stacked on the reels. This excludes the possibility of landing a full screen of matching symbols and getting a bigger payout.
Landing a decent 3 of a kind win on the reels of Classic Fruit can be a challenge, but luckily two of a kind wins with the Cherry, Orange, Lemon and Apple symbols are quite frequent.
This is the main reason why players can get frequent small payouts and keep their balance in place most of the time.

Conclusion.text:
Classic Fruit is definitely not the game you would want to play if you are aiming to win big. The slot simply doesn’t have the potential for big payouts, since the top prize per payline in the slot is set at 200 coins.
Players can get small to medium payouts during base play but they won’t make a big impact on the positive side of your balance.
Simply put there are other better slots coming from 1x2 Gaming that you can try if you want to win big.

title: Downtown
overview:
Downtown
    
        Play Downtown demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Downtown is a solid low-medium variance slot with a look stolen from Sin City and some rather weak visuals. It makes up for this with an RTP of 97.7% and a nicely paced experience with regular free spins and bonus rounds.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Downtown is, more or less, an unlicensed Sin City game. Several characters are lifted almost completely from Frank Miller’s masterpiece of minimalist art and maximised misogyny.
For those unfamiliar with the comic book and its film adaptations, this slot brings that dark 1930s noir-inflected crime comics to the spinning reels.
The symbols do their best to mimic the art of the comic and film, both of which went for high contrast black and white.
It’s a shame that the whole theme is tainted by being rather weakly imitative, rather than a quality pastiche.

media.caption: Visual design is not a masterpiece, but animations work quite well

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The visuals are a bit of a letdown, anyone familiar with the source material can see the poor quality of the imitation in the artwork.
However, the animations are clean enough and once you get into the game the style grows on you.
The sound design is faintly irritating, but as with most slots, you can turn off the effects that are most bothersome.

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay is at least solid in Downtown. The main game is a standard three by five-reel game with regular bonus hits to switch things up.
These bonus games (details below) are the main way in which the game breaks up its gameplay and allow for the game to take on a pleasing pace.
The unfortunate downside to Downtown’s regular bonus wins is that, of course, their regularity makes for much smaller wins each time you do hit one.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There are two main bonus features.
The first is a bonus game which is triggered by hitting three or more of the ‘police cell’ Scatter symbols. While these pay out 30, 100 and 200 coins for hitting 3, 4 or 5 Scatter symbols respectively they also trigger a bonus round in which you get to shoot at various targets. Each target you hit pays out a bonus amount.
The second bonus are the ‘femme fatale’ Free Spin symbols which give you 5 free spins for hitting 3 symbols, 10 for hitting 4 symbols and 15 if you manage to land five.
The main change to the reels for the free spins is that all payouts are doubled.
There is also a wild symbol that will substitute for any other symbol barring the Scatter and Free Spin symbols.

media.caption: Bonus game feature for scatter symbol hits
Special symbols explained

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The 97.7% return to player is one of the main draws of Downtown and reflects the generally high RTP of slots from 1x2 Gaming.
The variance is not very high on this game with its regular medium sized payouts on the bonuses. So factor that into your bankroll and strategic considerations.
The site we tested allowed a bet per spin from £/$/€0.05 per spin up to £/$/€75.00 per spin. Though this will vary across platforms.

media.caption: High symbols paytable

Conclusion.text:
The main appeal of Downtown is its frequent bonus rounds that make for a fun gaming experience. Unfortunately, this makes for small bonus wins when you do win, and the whole visual style of the slot is a little tacky looking.
If you can get past the visuals and are looking for a fun, low-medium variance slot this might be one of the better experiences for you.

title: El Toreo
overview:
El Toreo
    
        Play El Toreo demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Like bullfighting itself, you might be better off giving this rather dull slot a miss. Average RTP and high variance are the main appeals.

Theme and Storyline.text:
El Toreo is based around the once romantic (and now rather grim) world of bullfighting. The symbols include a furious bull, the roses that are traditionally thrown to winning matadors, and the matador himself. The matador here looks like the hero on the cover of a cheap romantic paperback.
The theme feels a little dated, and the style more so, but there are still a few unironic matador slots kicking around. If that’s your jam, this slot has you covered.

media.caption: Big win with 2 expanding Wild symbols

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are a definite let down for this slot. The art style feels cheap and looks tawdry. The romance novel style doesn’t help the look and robs it of style and character.
The soundtrack is unobtrusive, but is rather bland and doesn’t mesh particularly well with the theme.
The animations are simple but at least they are clear and easy to follow.

media.alt: El Toreo slot win right to left
media.caption: Wins can be calculated right-to-left way too

Gameplay.text:
El Toreo is built on a pretty basic slot format. There are five reels, each of which has three rows. There are ten win lines and a simple free spin bonus (see below for details).
The only special symbols are the wild and scatter. There is no gamble feature.
In other words, if you’ve played a few slots, you have a pretty good idea exactly how this one is going to play.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol. When the Wild symbol lands, it expands to cover the whole reel.
Three or more Scatter symbols trigger a Free Spin bonus. As well as the payout for the Scatters, the player receives 10 free spins.
During Free Spins, the Wild symbol is sticky. This means that any Wild that lands, stays in place for any subsequent free spins.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.08%, pretty much exactly on our yardstick for average of roughly 96%. We won’t quibble over 0.08 percentage points if you won’t.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€50.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is high, which makes it a good match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Full paytable for El Toreo slot machine

Conclusion.text:
El Toreo is a bit of a whole heap of bull… fighting. The visuals are uninspiring and leave a lot to be desired in terms of atmosphere and style.
The gameplay is similarly basic. The whole thing lacks the kind of flare you would expect from a matador themed slot. This has none of the pageantry of a bullfight.
When you add in the mediocre RTP, the number of pros are dwindling to more or less just the high volatility which allows players to apply our slot strategies. That said, there are plenty of slots that better fit that goal.
This slot hardly gets us interested enough to charge it, let alone properly gore it.

title: Golden Dragon (GameArt)
overview:
Golden Dragon (GameArt)
    
        Play Golden Dragon (GameArt) demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Golden Dragons fly and writhe across the reels in this beautiful slot with solid but simple features, an RTP of 96.00% and low volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Golden Dragon by GameArt is a pretty standard Chinese-themed slot. It uses the typical red and gold colours scheme, framing the reels with a dragon statue in gold leaf at either end and decorating the reels themselves with intricate masks and icons relating to dragons.
While the slot doesn’t do much different with its style, it does it to a very high quality and, if you are fond of this sort of theme, there are few better versions of it.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics of Gold Dragon are a little over detailed, but the slot makes that work. The feel of the reels is much less an ordered series of rows and reels and much more a New Year’s Day parade of gold and jade.
The animations add to this atmosphere, adding a firework-like sparkle to the proceedings.
The music is a well-composed bit of pseudo-classical Chinese music which does the job of setting the scene and is sufficiently subtle as to allow the player to have it on without it turning into a kind of water torture.

media.caption: Win in the Golden Dragon slot machine

Gameplay.text:
Golden Dragon is a five reel slot with four rows and fifty win lines.
It has a nice little gamble feature that allows the player to play double or nothing by betting on the colour of the next card off a deck containing infinite cards. There is also a free spin bonus to spice things up.
On the whole, the gameplay elements are fairly typical of modern slots.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol. In Golden Dragon, the Wilds are stacked, leading to some big multiway wins at times.
The Scatter only appears on reels two, three and four. If the player lands a Scatter on all three reels in one spin, they pay out four times the bet per spin and trigger a Free Spin Bonus.
The Free Spin Bonus starts with five free spins. During the free spins, stacked Wilds are more frequent on the reels and the Scatter remains in play, paying out as usual and adding five more spins should the player hit another three in one go.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.00%, spot on our yardstick for average which we hold to be around 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.25 up to a maximum of $/£/€125.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is low, which makes it a very poor match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our strategies tend to target highly volatile slots.

media.caption: Full paytable of the Golden Dragon slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Golden Dragon is a good example of its kind. While it doesn’t do much that is new, what makes it stand out is the quality with which it does it.
The theme is a tired one, but in Golden Dragon it is given some new life by high-quality visuals. The gameplay is simple, but compelling. Even the RTP is exactly what we consider average.
The main downside from our point of view is the low volatility. However, if low volatility works for you, this slot might be a good choice.

title: 300 Shields
overview:
300 Shields
    
        Play 300 Shields demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: A high variance slot coming from NextGen Gaming with a popular Spartan theme. Get to the last level in the free spins bonus and all wins with a Wild symbol involved will come with a massive 300 multiplier.

300 Shields review.text: 300 Shields is most likely one of the most popular video slots coming from the NextGen Gaming factory. At first look the slot doesn’t seem like it has a lot to offer. But once you take a look at the bonus feature you will see that 300 Shields has the potential for massive payouts thanks to the maximum 300 win multiplier which players can get in the free spins bonus. This is the main reason why this slot is so popular at NextGen Gaming casinos and why it’s worth trying out for real play.

media.caption: Simple win with Wild symbol in 300 Shields slot machine

Theme and Visual Details.text:
The theme of the game comes from the world known Spartan legend about King Leonidas and his army of 300 brave Spartans. The reels of the game are set in a wheat field in ancient Greece, but we can’t say that the visual details are on the top level.
But this is to be expected as 300 Shields is an older slot and the designers focused more on the payouts in the game rather than on the visual appearance.

Gameplay.text:
Like in many other NextGen Gaming slots the reels of the game seem to spin slower than in most other slots. This contributes for a slow gameplay which can be dull at times, since the base play payouts are not too impressive.
The only real excitement starts when two Scatters hit the reels and you’re eagerly waiting for the third one to strike.

media.caption: Collect scatter symbols and get up to a 20 free spins bonus game
Gameplay video

Bet sizes and payouts.text:
300 Shields is a 25 payline slot where players can place bets ranging anywhere from $0.25 up to $12.5 per spin.
As expected, the slot comes with a high variance and an RTP value of 95.29%, which is a bit lower than in most video slots.

media.caption: Full paytable of 300 Shields slot machine

Bonus features.text:
The Wild symbol in the game is the Warrior and it comes with a maximum payout of 1,000 coins for landing 5 of them on a winning payline. The Wild Warrior can land on all of the reels and will replace for all of the symbols in the slot, except for the Scatter Shield symbol.
The Scatter symbol can also land on all of the reels and has a maximum payout of 100 times the total stake for landing 5 of them on the reels. But the fun starts even with 3 Scatters on the reels which trigger the Battle Feature.
When the Battle Feature begins, the player is awarded with 5 free spins where all wins with a Wild symbol involved will be doubled in size. The goal of the feature is to collect as many Scatters as possible and get to the last level.
If you collect two or more Shields during the initial 5 free spins you will get an extra 5 free spins where all Wild wins will be multiplied by 5. If you manage to collect 6 or more Shields in total from the first and second series you will get a third series of 5 free spins where all payouts will be multiplied by 25. The end goal is to collect 12 or more Shields which will award a fourth series of 5 free spins where all wins with a Wild symbol will be multiplier by 300.
This way all you need is one 5 of a kind win with a Wild symbol involved in order to get a big payout. The best part is that if you get 3 Shields in a single spin during the feature the current series is re-triggered with an additional 5 free spins. This means that you can get a big number of free spins in the last series and hopefully a big payout, thanks to the 300 multiplier attached to the Wild Warrior.

media.alt: 300 Shields slot huge free spins win
media.caption: After reaching stage 4 of the free spins bonus game there is big chance for a huge win
Hit 3 scatters for free spins bonus

Conclusion.text: 300 Shields is a video slot which will definitely catch your attention once you see what the bonus feature has to offer. The visual details and animations used in the slot are not too attractive, but there’s much more about this slot than meets the eye. With a Wild Win Multiplier ranging up to 300 players can easily score a big payout in the bonus feature, if they are lucky enough to reach the last level.

overview:

about_game: A While on the Nile is a great NextGen Gaming slot featuring the Superbet option. Play the game on the top Superbet level and get the top x10 win multiplier of the Wild symbol.

A While on the Nile review.text:
A While on the Nile is an older but still very popular video slot coming from NextGen Gaming. This is a Superbet game, which has the potential for payouts ranging up to 10,000 times the total stake in a single spin.
In order to have a chance to land this kind of payout you will need to play on the maximum Superbet level, setting your minimum bet size at $3.5 per spin. Because of this A While on the Nile is a game which will require a higher starting bankroll if you want to optimize your chances of winning big.

Theme and Visual Details.text:
The game is inspired by Ancient Egypt with Cleopatra and the Pharaoh as main game symbols. In terms of visual details, the slot is not on the top level, but this is to be expected from a little bit outdated title.
But even so the symbols in the game are well designed and the choice of colors is spot on, giving the slot a vintage appearance.

media.caption: Visibility of actual winning lines is little worse

Gameplay.text: The gameplay in A While on the Nile is quite fun, since you never know when a big number of Wilds will land on the reels. With the Superbet option activated any payouts from all Wild wins are significantly bigger, which makes the slot even more exciting to play.

media.caption: Gameplay video featuring free spins

Bet size, payouts and RTP.text:
A While on the Nile is designed as a 50 payline slot, meaning that the bet size can range anywhere from $0.50 up to $125 per spin.
Playing with the Superbet option will in return increase your total stake size. Depending whether you are playing with the Superbet on level 1, 2, 3, 4 or 5 the minimum bet size can be $1, $1.5, $2.5, $3 or $3.5 per spin, while the maximum bet per spin can go up to $875 per spin.
The game comes with a high variance and an RTP value of 95.63%.

media.caption: Game's full paytable
This is one of NextGen's games with Super Bet feature

Bonus features.text:
The first detail you will notice about the game is the Superbet option. As we said before, there are 5 levels in total, which increase your total bet size in return, but the benefits from using the Superbet option are well worth the extra funds.
Each Superbet level will increase the win multiplier of the Wild symbol. So, depending whether you are playing on level 1, 2, 3, 4 or 5, the Wild will have an attached multiplier of x2, x4, x6, x8 or x10.
The Wild symbol in the game is the Pharaoh and it can land on reels 2, 3 and 4 only. It can land stacked across these reels and will substitute for all other symbols in the game, except for the Scatter symbols.
A While on the Nile comes with two Scatter symbols, both triggering a separate bonus feature.
The Scarab can land on reels 1, 3 and 5 only and triggers the Scarab Bonus Feature. This is a cash pick and win bonus where you make picks on the screen and get cash prizes in return. The Scarab Bonus will end when the Collect symbol is revealed.
The Jewel Scatter can land on reels 2, 3 and 4 only. When this happens the free spins bonus is triggered where the player is awarded with 5 free spins. If another trio of Jewels land on the reels during the feature, extra 5 free spins are awarded. During the free spins bonus Extra Wild symbols are added to the three central reels.

media.caption: How Scarab Bonus symbol works

Conclusion.text:
A While on the Nile is an attractive video slot which is a predecessor of the more modern version of this game, Merlin’s Millions Superbet HQ. Both slots have the same bonus features and payouts, the only difference being in the game symbols and visual details.
In order to maximize your chances of winning big in this game you will need to play on the top Superbet level. This will require a bigger starting bankroll, but you can win a lot more in one lucky spin.

title: Big Foot
overview:
Big Foot
    
        Play Big Foot demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Can you prove Bigfoot is real or was it just a squirrel? Find out by playing Bigfoot, a fun cartoonish slot machine with some nice bonus features. Just bear in mind the 95.013% RTP and medium to low variance.

Theme and Story Line.text:
If you go down to the woods today you’re sure of a big-footed surprise… Big Foot takes you on the trail of America’s mythical Sasquatch, a hairy man-like creature that lives in the woods and is only ever available for super grainy photographs taken by the least credible of people.
If you track him down in this game though, and you might just make your fortune.

media.caption: Simple win in Bigfoot slot machine

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The Big Foot in this game is kind of cute to look at and he comes with little cartoon animals, enthusiastic bigfoot believers and gigantic corn roasting on the cob.
Unfortunately, the cutesy vibe is let down massively by the animation which is very badly optimised. It can be jerky and slow despite not being very high-def. The reels take forever to spin and all the animations are dragged out. Coupled with the poor performance this really kills any sense of exciting pacing. You can spend forever waiting for the action to catch-up.
Apart from this the game’s not too badly designed (although the images look like they might have been produced in Microsoft Paint), the music is alright and the setting is well created.

media.caption: Symbols are nicely drawn

Gameplay.text:
Gameplay is pretty fun once you get past the slow spinning reels. There are plenty of features: two bonuses (more on which below) and a gamble feature which allows you to bet either red or black on the next card or go quadruple-or-nothing with a suit bet feature.
These various features help to break up the gameplay nicely in this otherwise typical 25 win line, five reel slot machine.

media.caption: Gameplay video with free spins feature

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There are two special symbols – a Wild (bigfoot) symbol and a Scatter (footprint) symbol.
The Wild symbol appears on reels 2, 3, and 4 and plays as any symbol except for Scatters. If you hit a Wild on all three reels though you also trigger a bonus game in which you must click on three of five sets of eyes that are glowing at you in the dark. Each set of eyes is revealed to be a forest creature and a prize is one depending on which creatures you find.
The biggest prize is for finding Bigfoot himself.
The Scatter symbol, on the other hand, pays out a multiple of your bet per spin: two scatters wins you 2-times your bet, three earns you 5, four earns you 15, and five wins you a nice, round 100-times your bet per spin.
If you hit three or more Scatters you also get 10 free spins. Free spins can be retriggered and are added to your Scatter win once done.

media.caption: Explanation of Bigfoot's features
Bigfoot's bonus game

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
You can determine exactly how many winlines to play by choosing any number from 1 to 25, which gives you some nice control over your variance per spin. Which is good as this is not a very high variance game and sometimes you wanna up your exposure to the big wins.
The RTP is given by the maker as an oddly precise: 95.013%. This is nothing to write home about as we tend to think of 96% as being about average and anything under this as being a bit disappointing.

media.caption: Bigfoot - paytable

Conclusions.text:
Big Foot is quite fun. It does sometimes suffer from some technical difficulties but once working right it can be a pleasure to play with nice design and fun features.
Its main downsides, however, are the lowish RTP and lack of opportunities for the really big wins that come with higher variance games.

title: Easy Slider
overview:
Easy Slider
    
        Play Easy Slider demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Hit the open road with a chopped hog between your legs, a biker chick for a passenger and mile after mile of straight driving ahead of you in Easy Slider. The game's setting is fun, but not as fun as the slider feature which allows you to decide what kind of game you’re playing. High-risk/high-reward or a smooth low-risk ride.

Theme and Storyline.text:
"The Menace is loose again, the Hell's Angels, the hundred-carat headline, running fast and loud on the early morning freeway, low in the saddle, nobody smiles, jamming crazy through traffic and ninety miles an hour down the center stripe, missing by inches...like Genghis Khan on an iron horse" - Hunter S Thompson, Hell’s Angels
Now the menace is loose again, this time in Easy Slider, a title that suggests Dennis Hopper’s end of the hippie era movie. It borrows its images from the Hell’s Angels’ patches with winged Aces and denim patches. What the average motorcycle outlaw might have to say on having their world milked for gambling profits, and indeed what the free-wheeling anti-capitalist characters of Easy Rider (1969) might want to add to it is perhaps a discussion for another time.
If you want a sense of freedom on the open road, and you wanna get it from an indoor slot, you could do worse than booting this one up.

media.caption: Easy Slider slot machine

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Like a lot of Nextgen’s output, the animations in Easy Slider are fun and frequently elaborate. But for some reason, less effort is put into the actual imagery which tends to look rather cheaply turned out and generically cartoonish.
Easy Slider suffers less from these problems than some due to its rather over the top setting, but even so, it certainly could be better looking with just a few small changes.

Gameplay.text:
The game plays as a five reel, 25 win-line slot with one or two features that slide in to enhance play.
The first feature is the titular slider. This allows you to choose which reel the Wild symbol will be stacked on. The further from reel one you place the slider the bigger the multiplier rewards for winning with Wild symbols, and the bigger your potential winnings in the bonus games (see below for more specifics on that).
There is also a black or red gamble feature, or if you’re feeling risk-frisky you can bet on the next suit for to quadruple your win. It is identical to many other Nextgen games and doesn’t quite fit with the aesthetic of Easy Slider but it’s always nice to have the option to ramp up your volatility if you fancy.

media.caption: NextGen's usual gamble feature
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The main way to spin up the big bucks in Easy Slider is to hit a big combo with the stacked Wild symbols. This is because Wild symbols gain a multiplier depending on where you place the slider. (See the Table below).
Note on the table that this also affects the "free games" with the multipliers doubling during the free spins.
Free spins are won by hitting three or more of the Scatter symbol. In this case as well as getting a payout which is a multiple of your bet-per-spin you also receive ten free spins with the enhanced Wild symbols on the reel of your choice.

media.caption: Explanation of the Slide-a-Wild bonus feature

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The RTP varies slightly depending on where you place the slider, but it is between 95.15% and 95.60%. Even at its highest percentage, it is still slightly below average for the industry.
The volatility is a little harder to put a finger on. By placing your slider on Reel 1 you can make the game relatively medium/low volatility whereas the further along from the Reel 1 you place the slider, the higher that volatility goes as combos become less likely but vastly more profitable.
You’ll have to experiment and decide what works best for your bankroll and strategies.

media.caption: Simple win in Easy Slider slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Easy Slider’s main selling point is the slider. If this innovation appeals to you, this is a great slot, if not it feels pretty average with most the play, features and RTP all being somewhat mediocre.
That said, it is always nice to see games trying new things so we’d tentatively recommend this to those who think the slider concept appeals.

title: Jackpot Jester 200000
overview:
Jackpot Jester 200000
    
        Play Jackpot Jester 200000 demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: This clever twist on the three reel slot adds a second slot game on top of the regular one. A high-variance treat for anyone brave enough to risk their winnings in the game’s different modes. The main downside is a small gaming screen and lowish RTP of 95.08%.

Theme and Storyline.text:
The exact theme of Jackpot Jester 200,000 is a little hard to place.
The whole game looks a bit odd. The goal seems to have been to recreate the actual experience of playing a pub fruit machine in a tropical swimming pool. One can only hope that everything is sufficiently waterproofed in this NextGen's slot machine.
That said, when you have a set of gameplay mechanics as interesting as this game, you don’t always need to package it in some sort of fancy storyline.

media.caption: Jackpot Jester 200000 slot machine

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are gorgeously clear in super hi-def. Unfortunately, they are also rather small; the frame around the actual game is huge and as a result, the buttons and symbols are all shrunk right down. This problem is compounded by the double reels that make up the game area.
Despite being so small the animations are smooth and the sound design is very unobtrusive, a little background electronica and some gentle splashing. The machine makes nice clunks and bleeps when the reels spin.
All in all its a bit of a work of art.

Gameplay.text:
If you wanted you could play this game as a three reel, five pay line slot machine. To do this, you just choose the 10 coin option (you have a lot of control over how much each coin is worth so this is really just a way of choosing game modes.
If you chose the 20 coin option though, your winnings are applied to the Super Game or 100 coin mode which we will come to in a sec.
You can also just hit "Collect" to cash out your Super Game coins. Keep the coins in the Super Game line though and once you have 100 coins there, you can switch to 100 coin mode.
The 100 coin mode switches the game to the upper tier of the machine. You still play three reels and five pay lines. In both 10 and 20 coin mode, all symbols are stacked except for the Jester and the Jester plays as a Wild symbol.
In 100 coin mode, the Jesters are stacked along with all the other symbols. The Jesters also switch from being Wild to Pay Any, effectively becoming Scatters.

media.caption: 2 paytables - depends whether you play basic game or 100 coins game mode
High level bet - 100 coins - gameplay
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text: There are no Bonuses or Free Spins in this game however the Jester symbol does act as both a Scatter and a Wild depending on context (see Gameplay for details).

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The RTP of 95.08% for Jackpot Jester 200,000 is a bit lower than we would like. The industry average is around 96% and coming nearly a full percentage point under that is not endearing.
Depending on how you play Jackpot Jester 200,000 this game can be either a medium volatility game (if you stick to 10 coin mode or regularly collect your Super Game coins; or it can be extremely high volatility game if you decide to roll your winnings over into the 100 coin mode.
Bet sizes are managed pretty simply by setting the coin size. For example, €/$/£0.05 coins in "20 coin mode", will make for a €/$/£1.00 bet per spin. The site we tested allowed coin sizes from €/$/£0.01 to €/$/£1.00. That means the spread of bets you can make are from €/$/£0.10 to €/$/£20 per spin.
This is fairly limited but a bet of €/$/£20.00 per spin would allow you to gamble €/$/£100 per spin once you switch to 100 coin mode.

media.caption: Betting options in Jackpot Jester 200000 slot machine

Conclusion.text:
With its unusual setup and ingeniously simple play style, Jackpot Jester 200,000’s gameplay probably suits the real high-variance speculator better than most other players.
To really enjoy it you have to be ready to gamble in 100 coin mode as much as possible.

title: King Kong 2016
overview:
King Kong 2016
    
        Play King Kong 2016 demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: From Skull Island to New York, King Kong 2016 comes a long way even travelling through time to 1933 when the original King Kong hit cinemas to universal applause. This high volatility slot is as temperamental as a giant ape, and only let down by its RTP of 95.14%.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Whether you have watched the 1933 cinematic classic King Kong, you still know the story beats through cultural osmosis. Images like Kong versus the T-rex, Fae Wray in the palm of the ape’s hand, biplanes circling the Empire State Building, and the immortal line "twas beauty killed the beast," have somehow stuck with all of us even as Peter Jackson’s remake seemed to be wholly ignored by audiences.
With anything that iconic, it is only a matter of time before someone turns it into a slot. In Kong’s case, it has happened dozens of times, but one of the better ones is King Kong 2016 from NextGen Gaming. The year refers to the game’s publication rather than some modernised update of the theme. The movie cameras are 1930s models and the aircraft are still biplanes.
Whether a classic movie makes for a classic slot, we will see.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
At the level of imagery, it certainly works. King Kong 2016 is elegantly designed with a visual style reminiscent of movie posters of that era.
The animations are clean and clear and make the whole game much more enjoyable and playable. The sound design is simple, but effective.
Overall at the visual level, the slot has a pleasant and unified tone.

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay, like the design, is simple and effective. There are five reels, each of which has three rows. There are 25 win lines to play with, and when you win, there is a simple double/quadruple or nothing gamble feature to play if you fancy upping the already very high volatility.
Nothing to write home from Skull Island about then, but covering the key bases.

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol fills in for all other symbols except the Scatter symbol. The Wild symbol also triggers the King Kong Goes Ape feature when a Wild lands on reel three.
The King Kong Goes Ape feature results in the Wild on reel three expanding to fill that reel and expands. There is also a chance that some of the symbols on reels two and four will also be turned into Wilds.
Hitting three Scatter symbols triggers the King Kong Smash feature. In this feature, you play a minigame in which King Kong tries to knock down biplanes. This round continues until Kong misses three planes. The number of planes he knocks down then determines how many free spins the player gets. Fifteen spins for one plane, up to 150 spins for six planes.
Once the number of free spins is determined, the player gets a chance to choose either the free spins or a mystery cash prize.
During the free spins – if the player chooses them – all wins are doubled. If you hit another three Scatters in a single free spin, you retrigger the same number of free spins that you already won. You don’t get to swing at the biplanes again.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 95.14%, a little under the yardstick for average that we use of 96%.
The range of bet on the site we tested ran the gamut from $/£/€0.25 per spin all the way up to a maximum of $/£/€250.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is very high, a fact that we really like. The higher the volatility the better the match a game is for our preferred strategies. Along with the gamble feature this makes up for the mildly disappointing return to player.

Conclusion.text:
King Kong 2016 may not be the classic that the movie it is based on is, but it is it pretty solid. It comes with great visuals, decent gameplay, some fun bonus games, and all the 1933 Kong references you could possibly want.
However, for us the main appeal is the high volatility which makes it a good pairing with our preferred strategies, and although we would prefer a higher return to player, we can still recommend this to our readers.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Medusa II bases its world around the semi-tragic story of Medusa and the heroic tale of Perseus who slew her. The snake-haired Gorgon of Greek myth appears in the game along with plenty of other ancient Greek style symbols.
Medusa, in the original tale was so unconscionably vile to look at that if you got a direct line of sight on her you’d turn to stone. Nextgen Gambling has taken a slightly different line on Medusa’s looks, and instead, she’s a gorgeous girl with snakes for hair and a very revealing Golden bikini top.

media.caption: Medusa II HQ has high quality visuals

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The theme is much better rendered than many other Ancient Greek inspired with really nice artwork on the symbols which are beautifully animated.
Visually it is one of the classiest (as well as Classical) of Nextgen’s offerings. The animation is slick as they come without being over-flashy.
It also comes with a snazzy score that seems lifted from something like Jason and the Argonauts, and does an excellent job setting the scene.

Gameplay.text:
Gameplay is perhaps where this slot is weakest. While the main gameplay is nicely paced it doesn’t come with much in the way of bells and whistles. In fact, there is not much to distinguish it from any other 243 win-ways slot with five reels.
There is no gamble feature or bonus games (see below) and so it is a little unimpressive in this regard.
There are two randomised features. In the first, a soldier can appear at the top of a random reel and turn all the symbols on that reel into Wilds.
In the second randomised feature, a number of reels (between two and all five) will fall into synch with each other and display the same symbols side by side.

media.caption: Wild symbols are stacked in Medusa II HQ slot
Simple win in Medusa II HQ slot
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
Although there are no bonus games, you can swing some Free Spins by hitting three or more Scatter symbols. This feature can be retriggered for additional 5 Free Spins.
The game’s set of Wild symbols are pretty standard in that they substitute for any other symbol except for the Scatter symbol. You can also win some cash by getting a Wild Combo. This pays out 20 times your bet for three Wilds in a "win-way," 50 times your bet for four, and a big prize of 500 times your bet for five in adjacent reels.

media.alt: Medusa 2 HQ scatters and wilds paytable
media.caption: Paytable for Scatter and Wild symbols

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
Being a 243 win-way slot, the bets are done on a per spin basis. The site we tested allowed between £/$/€0.25 and £/$/€50.00 per spin. This might exclude those at the extreme low-end and high-end of the bankroll market.
Other sites may well offer a better spread.
The RTP of 97.07% is pretty tasty being a bit above average. A bit above average is also a good description of the game’s volatility.

media.caption: High symbols paytable

Conclusion.text:
Medusa is a lovely looking slot that plays nicely and has a decent RTP. While it may not excel except visually, there is really very little to detract from it and so it is a definite recommend from us.
It could be improved with a few little bonus games to change the pacing a little though.

Merlins Millions Superbet HQ review.text:
Merlins Millions Superbet HQ is a video slot coming from the NextGen Gaming portfolio.

Theme and Visual Details.text:
The game is inspired by Merlin, who was a world famous wizard from the time of King Arthur and Camelot.
The designers did a great job with the game theme. On the left side of the reels you will see a fun animation of Merlin showing off some of his magic. The slot has an attractive appearance thanks to these modern animations and the vibrant choice of colors.

media.caption: Stacked wilds on middle reels offer a good chance for a big win

Gameplay.text: The gameplay in Merlins Millions Superbet HQ is quite fun as players can score big wins out of the blue. As in most other Superbet slots this is due to the extra features which this option brings. The excitement on the reels in this slot rises as the Wilds hit the screen, along with multipliers of up to x10.

media.caption: Gameplay video featuring two of the bonuses - Owl bonus feature and free spins

Bet size RTP and payouts.text:
Merlins Millions Superbet HQ is a 50 payline slot, so the bet size can range from $0.50 up to $125 per spin. This bet size is without the Superbet option active.
You can set the Superbet on 5 levels in total, which in return will increase your total stake by plus 1, 2, 4, 5 and 6 times the basic bet. This means that the minimum bet size with the Superbet on the top fifth level will be $3.5 per spin, while the maximum will go up to $875 per spin.
Make no mistake; this is a high variance game with an RTP value of 95.63% which can pay big, but can also eat a lot of balance in return.

media.caption: Merlins Millions Superbet full paytable

Bonus features.text:
The Superbet option in the game will add a win multiplier to the Wild symbol. Depending whether the Superbet is set on level 1, 2, 3, 4 or 5 the Wild symbol will have a win multiplier of x2, x4, x6, x8 or x10.
The Wild symbol in the game is Merlin himself and it can land on reels 2, 3 and 4 only. The best detail about the Wild is that it can land stacked on the reels, so you can easily get 3 Wild Reels in a single spin.
The slot also comes with two Scatter symbol. The first one is the Owl, landing on reels 1, 3 and 5, while the second is the Orb landing on reels 2, 3 and 4 only.
The Owl triggers the Owl Bonus Feature where players need to make picks from the Owl symbols on the reels and get cash prizes in return. The bonus ends when the Collect symbol is uncovered.
The Orb symbol triggers the free spins bonus where the player is awarded with 5 free spins. More free spins can be won during the feature if another 3 Orbs land on the reels.
During the bonus round Merlin stands beside the reels and awards extra Wild symbols on the three central reels. This is when the player has the biggest chances of getting three Wild Reels on the screen and a guaranteed big payout, if playing on the top Superbet level.

Collect cash winnings in the Owl bonus feature

Conclusion.text:
Merlins Millions Superbet HQ is an interesting and attractive NextGen Gaming slot which can pay big during base play and in the bonus round.
But in order to win big you will need to play on the top Superbet level, setting your minimum bet size at $3.5 per spin. Still this extra bet size is well worth the risk as it can yield the biggest payouts in return.
This means that you will need to risk a bigger balance in this game in order to maximize your chances of winning big. The rest is all up to Merlin.

title: Wonder Hounds 95
overview:
Wonder Hounds 95
    
        Play Wonder Hounds 95 demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Wonder Hounds gives you three charming main characters (all well-dressed doggos) and a beautiful looking slot with some fun randomised events to play. Just a shame about the low RTP (95.16%).

Theme and Storyline.text:
Nextgen’s Wonder Hounds slot machine is set in a world of intelligent and extremely dapper canines. The dogs you meet in this world include Ace, an old-timey fighter pilot; Winchester, a country gent in deerstalker and monocle; and Jinse the Asian concubine of one or both of them.
The characters are fun and although there is very little real story, it is easy to project a classic Chicken Run style competition between the English Winchester and the American Ace.

media.caption: Wonder Hounds 95 has high quality visual design

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The NextGen Gaming do a good line in animations when they want to. Wonder Hounds is definitely one of the good ones with a lovely set of animations and plenty of character worked into every symbol – apart from of course the ubiquitous and slightly dull Ace to Nine symbols.
The soundtrack, on the other hand, is just fairly unobnoxious, and certainly won’t be winning any awards.

Gameplay.text:
The game is a 25 win-line, five reel slot. The number of lines you can play is fixed.
Overall gameplay is fun, the game has plenty of little-animated distractions to keep you interested despite its lack of complicated bonus games or gamble options.

media.caption: Despite lower volatility big wins can be achieved in Wonder Hounds 95
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There are two special symbols: a Wild and a Scatter.
The Wild substitutes for any symbol apart from the Scatter. You can also win using a Wild symbol combo if it falls on a win line. A nice twist is that at the end of every spin up to one random Wonderhound per reel may switch to a Wild symbol.
If you hit three or more Scatters you win 8, 12 or 15 free spins for 3, 4 or 5 Scatters respectively. At the start of these free spins, a random number of Wilds (between 1 and 15) appear on the reels. For all the free spins any Wilds that are hit lock in place for the rest of the free spins.

media.caption: Each Wild symbol locks in place for the rest of the free spin feature

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The RTP of 95.16% is a bit disappointing, falling almost a full percentage below the industry yardstick we use of 96%.
Coupled with medium to low volatility this slot machine doesn’t make a great match for our preferred strategies.
The other disadvantage of this slot is the lack of ability to choose how many win lines to play. You are locked into the full 25 every spin so you are unable to manipulate volatility or bet per spins to as fine a degree as you might like.
The site we tested allowed for bets per spin of €/£/$0.25 to €/£/$250. This is a very good spread and allows for most bankroll sizes to play.

media.caption: Wonder Hounds 95 top symbols paytable
Scatter symbol paytable

Conclusion.text:
Wonder Hounds is fun to look at and fun to play.
However, it lets the side down when it comes to its RTP, volatility and lack of features.
It could have been a great slot, but on the whole, ends up being very hard to really recommend. Disappointing.

title: Blaze Of Ra
overview:
Blaze Of Ra
    
        Play Blaze Of Ra demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Worship Ra the falcon-headed sun god in this ancient Egyptian-themed slot. Just be aware of the decent RTP of 96.40% and the medium-high volatility.

Theme and Style.text:
The Blaze of Ra slot focuses on the ancient Egyptian god Ra. This falcon-headed deity stands watch over the reels with his predatory eyes locked on the player’s actions. He stands atop a rock that is whipped about by a fog of blown sands, as the pyramids loom large in the background.
Blaze of Ra pits the player in a game of chance against the gods. The player will need some luck and maybe even divine intervention to beat the god and escape with the treasures.
This game brings a new angle to a well-worn slot theme and will appeal to fans of ancient Egyptian myth as well as specific fans of the myth of Ra.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Blaze of Ra is a slot with beautiful imagery. The animated avatar of Ra that stands over the game strikes his staff to spin the reels and set the player on a new path of fate.
The reels themselves are prettily drawn with a 3D look and some highly polished hieroglyphic-inspired visuals—a lotus flower, an ankh, and various gods, appear on the symbols along with the usual melange of ace to jack symbols.

Gameplay.text:
This slot, Blaze of Ra, has five reels. Each reel has four rows on it, allowing plenty of space for the forty winlines.
A simple bonus feature provides some variety (more details below), but like Blaze of Ra’s slot theme, everything is pretty classic with just a hint of a twist.
For example, there is a simple nudge feature that gives players a free respin when two or more stacked Wilds land on a reel. The Wilds are nudged down two extra places and the rest of the symbols are spun for a second time.
On any given round, the player’s maximum win is capped at 2,000x the player’s bet.

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbols carry an image of Ra on them and substitutes for all other symbols. The exception is the Bonus symbol that has a scarab image on it.
The Bonus symbol always islands with either a 1 or a 2 on it. When three or more Bonus symbols land anywhere on the reels, the Free Spin Bonus will trigger. The number of spins is dictated by the sum of all the numbers on the Bonus symbols.

title: Jammin' Jars
overview:
Jammin' Jars
    
        Play Jammin' Jars demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: A fun fruit based cascade game, with an RTP of 96.83% and a couple of nice features. A pleasant variation on the slot format, with some potential for big wins.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Set in the most disco greengrocers you’ve ever seen, Jammin’ Jars ensures you get your 
  five fruit and veg a day even as you party under its disco-ball. With spotlights and dancefloor glow patterns in the background, it is a cheerful slot that Push Gaming have done their best to kit out with plenty of vaguely jam based features.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The animations are clean and well rendered, with high def visuals and nicely drawn symbols. The physics of the falling fruit is nicely done and the win animations are quick and varied, making for a visual fruit-salad that is constantly changing.
The music is a truly horrible funk-beat that is best muted immediately on startup. Unfortunately, there is no option to turn just the music off which means you will also miss out on the actually very good sound design for the game mechanics.

media.caption: You can see some nice winnings with just one Jar symbol if you manage to hit it few times in one spin

Gameplay.text:
Jammin’ Jars is played on an eight by eight cascade-style grid. It offers quite a unique gameplay, which is different than what you might be used to from most popular slots.
On each spin, stacked tiles fall in from the top and are then removed from the game when they are part of a winning combination. This allows a cascade mechanism to kick in, bringing down more tiles from above to fill the empty spaces left by your win. If the new tiles trigger another win it all goes into your pile of winnings for that spin.
Accompanying this are a few well-designed features that complement the theme of the game and are nice variations on the usual set of features you might expect from a slot.
Variety is the spice of life, and it is nice to see games like Jammin’ Jars innovating with the slot machine format a bit.

media.caption: Hitting 3 Jars symbols gives you the free spins bonus
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There are three bonus features.
The first is the Wild jam jar symbol which falls at random.
The jar also gains a multiplier each time it is part of a win. The second win with a given Wild symbol results in a double payout, the third in a triple and so on. The jar remains in place during the cascade.
If you manage to land three Wild symbols in one spin (this includes any cascades you trigger) then you trigger the free spins bonus.
During free spins, when a Wild is part of a win it moves at random into an empty space left by the win before the cascade falls. The jar, once moved, remains in place during the cascade. During the next spin, it then moves to another adjacent space.
The result of combining multiple Wilds with cascades and constantly increasing multipliers mean that this bonus can result in absolutely massive wins if it goes well.
The third feature can be triggered when you win nothing on a spin. In this case, the game could add a random number of giant symbols all of the same kind but of varying sizes to the board. These act like every square they cover is one of the same fruit as the giant symbol.

media.alt: Multiple wilds with high multiplier count
media.caption: If you are lucky you can win big when more Jar symbols show up and raise the multiplier after each winning

media.alt: Jammin' Jars no win special feature
media.caption: No-win spin can turn into a winning one by chance with a special feature of Jammin' Jars

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The RTP for this game is a decent 96.83%. This is a little over the average of around 96%.
Wins tend to be very small from just combos of fruit. The big wins come from hitting the bonus features. As a result, the game can be quite high variance, a fact to bear in mind when working out your plan for bet sizing.

media.caption: Full paytable of Jammin' Jars slot

Conclusion.text:
Jammin’ Jars is a fun, fast-paced ride that is worth getting on just for the novelty of it.
The variance means there can be long periods of not much happening but when it comes to life, Jammin’ Jars is a ton of fun and with a decent RTP to go with it, this is a slot we can really recommend.

Theme and Storyline.text:

The Wild Ship Feature is triggered at random at the end of a spin in the base game. When triggered, the Wild Ship feature adds a set of Wild Ship Symbols to the reels and wins are recalculated.
The Free Spins Feature is triggered when three or more Scatters land anywhere on either reel or across both reels.
When a player lands the Free Spin feature, each Scatter symbol "launches" a Wild Shield symbol onto a random spot on the other reel. These stay in place for the duration of the free spins.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Bonanza Megaways is an extravagant, mining based offering from Big Time Gaming, which takes the hunt for treasures underground.
With a mining cart theme and a range of symbols from precious stones, gold bricks, mining carts and dynamite the imagery is on point.

Gameplay.text:

These spins come with multipliers and a new Scatter symbol that can trigger further free spins. The multipliers add up quickly with each "Reaction" adding x1 to the multiplier.
The result is the more times you hit a winning combination the bigger the multiplier making for the exponential growth of winnings during bonus rounds.

title: Golden Offer
overview:
Golden Offer
    
        Play Golden Offer demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Golden Offer is a neat little slot with great features, high volatility, and a decent RTP (96.03%).

Theme and Storyline.text:
Golden Offer is a fairly generic Chinese themed slot, using mostly the imagery of Chinese statuary, pearls and the ying-yang symbol. As with most of this kind of slots, the colour scheme is all red and gold and there are coins with square holes in them all over the shop when you hit a big win.
Despite using many of the same design elements as other slots in its thematic ballpark, Golden Offer does feel a little different thanks to its subtle changes to the theme. The backgrounds are stone walls instead of the usual rooftop scene, and there are no red curtains anywhere to be seen (both being the basic version of the backdrop for a theme of this kind).
Overall, it is a classy version of an otherwise somewhat overtired theme.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are one of the main draws for Golden Offer. With very little flare, they are beautifully designed examples of understatement. The background and reels go well together, and the visuals avoid clashing and work nicely as a group.
The animations are done with a similarly light touch. The reels have a satisfying weight to their spins, with a well-designed system to slow down and emphasise the tension when the Bonus symbols start falling.
The sounds work well with these animations, tying the whole thing together. It cannot be stressed enough how much a good set of spin and win sounds can elevate a simple slot into an immersive experience.

media.caption: Base game win in the Golden Offer slot machine

Gameplay.text:
Red Tiger Gaming has opted for an unusual set up of reels in Golden Offer. The 3-5-5-5-3 structure makes an elongated octagon of the base game. There are forty win lines across these unusual reels.
To spice up the play, there is the Golden Offer bonus which is an interesting twist on the bonus genre, playing like a miniature Deal or No Deal. There are also a number of randomly triggered features. All this is covered in detail in the section below.
The gameplay overall is interesting enough to keep players immersed, while also giving the basics the room they need to work.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all other symbols except the Golden Offer symbol.
Three Bonus symbols trigger a unique bonus game: the Golden Offer Bonus. During this bonus, four monetary bonuses are randomly generated. The player is offered them one by one and can accept the offer, or reject it in favour of the next one. The last offer is automatically accepted if the player reaches it.
There are also four lion features. These features are triggered at random and occur before the reels stop.
The Special Reels Feature removes all low value symbols, making for bigger wins. The Lion’s Nudge moves the reels to ensure the largest possible wins. Wild Reels turn select reels into all Wilds. Finally, Swap Tiles switches out random tiles with high-value symbols.

media.caption: Big win in the Golden Offer slot

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.03%, almost exactly the same as our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€20.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is high, making it an excellent match for our preferred slot machine strategies. We target the highest possible volatility with our slot strategies.

media.caption: Full paytable of the Golden Offer slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Golden Offer takes excellent graphics and an unassuming style onto which it adds an interesting bonus game, random features, and a decent RTP.
The high volatility also matches well with our slot machine strategies.
Overall we highly recommend this slot.

title: Treasures of Egypt
overview:
Treasures of Egypt
    
        Play Treasures of Egypt demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Treasures of Egypt is one of the treasures that can be safely left interred. The middling volatility and low RTP (94%) means this slot is better left buried in the desert.

Theme and Storyline.text:
The tombs of ancient Egypt are a rich source of modern myth, from the "curse of the mummy" to the exploits of Indiana Jones, but nowhere are they as ubiquitous as in the world of slots.
Treasures of Egypt doesn’t add much to distinguish itself from the considerable number of other Ancient Egypt slots. It offers a background of columns and hieroglyphs while the symbols are a set of canopic jars, papyrus and sarcophagus masks.
If you like Ancient Egypt, you might well get along with this slot, but it seems unlikely you’ll get on better with this than any other.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Treasures of Egypt does make up for its unimaginative take on Ancient Egypt by rendering it well. The slot has good graphics. The background is pretty and feels alive thanks to a series of looping animations of sand shifting and scarabs scuttling, and the reels have a range of distinctive and well drawn images, all taken from the Egyptian wing of any well-stocked museum.
The sound design is very well put together. Spinning the reels triggers the sound of heavy stones being rolled past each other and the music has a lilting North African style that fits the atmosphere of the game perfectly.

media.caption: Win in the Treasures of Egypt slot machine

Gameplay.text:
Treasures of Egypt is a five reel slot with three rows and up to twenty-five win lines. Players can adjust the number of lines they wish to play.
There is a simple gamble feature allowing the player to bet double or nothing on the colour of the next card, or quadruple or nothing on the suit.
Along with this is a fast-paced Free Spin bonus, which should hit relatively frequently thanks to the medium volatility of the game.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol.
Three or more Scatter symbols trigger a Free Spin bonus. Three Scatter symbols gets the player a single free spin while five will get the player ten free spins.
The Free Spin bonus can be retriggered.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
MrSlotty does not provide information regarding return to player or volatility on any of its games. We do not feel comfortable recommending any slot that is not transparent with its stats. RTP determines how good value a slot is and volatility is key in bankroll management and determining the kind of slot strategy you want to use.
Other sites have listed the RTP as 94.00%. If correct, this RTP is far too low for us to recommend this slot.
The range of bets on the site we tested started from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.01 per line. The player can play any number of lines between 1 and 25. The maximum bet on the site we tested was $/£/€25.00 per spin.
The volatility on this slot is medium.

media.caption: Full paytable of the Treasures of Egypt slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Due to the hazy RTP information, this slot is not one that we can recommend. Additionally, the medium volatility is also too low to pair well with our preferred slot strategies.
When coupled with the somewhat overdone theme and limited gameplay options, we strongly recommend looking elsewhere for your ancient Egyptian slot fix.

overview:

about_game: Poor RTP (94.0%) makes this slot less like diamond in the rough and more like coal in your stocking.

Theme and Storyline.text:
777 Diamonds uses a few classic slot symbols like the Bar, Cherry and Bell to create an old style one-armed bandit feel. However, the main twist is that everything is rendered as precious stones. The Cherries are ruby orbs on emerald stems, the bells are cut from yellow sapphires, and, of course there are plenty of actual diamonds on the reels too.
The theme makes for a gentle twist on a familiar form.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Like many simple one-armed bandit inspired slots, the graphics aren’t too fancy. The symbols are well drawn and the animations clear but basic.
The music is a gentle piano track that might be a little low energy for a slot. It’s pretty relaxing, but most people play slots for excitement, which this rather undercuts.
The overall effect is of a gentle lounge style game, rather than the high speed flashy style of many slots.

media.caption: Win in the 777 Diamonds slot

Gameplay.text:
777 Diamonds uses a standard five reel, three row format. This comes with 25 win lines.
There is a gamble feature which players can use after a winning spin. It is the standard infinite deck of cards in which players can choose to bet their winnings either in a quadruple-or-nothing bet on the next card’s suit or a double-or-nothing bet on the card’s colour.
The gameplay is simple and pretty standard. That might not appeal to everyone, but it puts it on a par with most of the competition.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Bonus symbol.
Three or more Bonus symbols on any one spin will award the player free spins. Three Bonus symbols gets a single free spin, four gets the player three free spins, and the maximum of five symbols gets the player ten free spins.
There are no additional bonuses to play.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 94.00%, much lower than our yardstick for average of roughly 96%. 94% is simply too expensive for us to recommend this slot and may explain the slot’s relatively low popularity in general.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.01 up to a maximum of $/£/€25.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a weak match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility. Given the low RTP, there is no volatility high enough to make this game appeal to us.

media.caption: Full paytable of the 777 Diamonds slot machine slot

Conclusion.text:
The poor RTP is enough to ruin this slot for us.
For those who are willing to pay the 6% per spin, the slot doesn’t offer very much for your buck. The style is simple, the bonuses are basic, and the volatility is middling.
Give this one a skip.
