title: Viva Las Vegas
overview:
Viva Las Vegas
    
        Play Viva Las Vegas demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Viva Las Vegas takes the glitz and glamour of a Vegas stage show and renders it dull. Plus the RTP is only 95.20%, no wonder the house always wins.

Theme and Storyline.text:
What is the quintessential Vegas experience? Perhaps casino floors with their deafening rattle of chips and cards, perhaps it was seeing Frank and Dean performing live, or cruising the strip with its myriad of buildings, each of which is a monument to excess and luxury.
If you are the design team at Red Rake Gaming, it is apparently show girls. There is a stylised version of the Bellagio fountains, card suits and the famous Welcome to Las Vegas sign, but the main symbols are all show girls, the background is a stage and the backing sound track is a theatre crowd applauding.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Given the off-kilter theme and titling of the slot, the actual graphics are largely fine. The symbols don’t all have a clear silhouette and so are easily lost in the funhouse.
But the combination of those symbols with the animations and the sound effects is pretty good. When you spin the wheels, a music hall track kicks in with some real rhythm to it and the reels give off their win and spin sounds with much aplomb.
Overall, the visuals are somewhat kitsch but it is top quality kitsch of the kind Vegas itself is famous for.

media.caption: Big win in the Viva Las Vegas slot

Gameplay.text:
Viva Las Vegas is played on five reels with four rows and fifty win lines.
A cascade system is in play, meaning that when a player hits a winning combination, the winning symbols are removed, allowing new symbols to fall down from above. Winning combinations are then recalculated and any additional cascades triggered.
There is also a free spin bonus to spice things up, which is triggered by hitting four or more consecutive cascades (see below for details).

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all other symbols.
If the cascade is triggered four or more times in a row on one single spin, then the player is awarded a Free Spin bonus with ten free spins. Any additional cascades over four will add a multiplier to any winnings during the free spins: x2 for the fifth cascade, x3 for six, and x10 if you get seven cascades in a row.
During the free spins the Vegas Sign symbol is Wild.

media.caption: Win in the Viva Las Vegas slot machine

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 95.20%, well below our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€50.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a poor match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Combining this with the low RTP results in us being unable to recommend this slot.

media.caption: Paytable of the Viva Las Vegas slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Viva Las Vegas has very little to offer. The theme and artwork are pretty dull, the slot lacks style, and the vig is extortionate.
The low RTP is the strongest argument against a recommendation for this slot, but the relatively low volatility doesn’t do it any favours either.
Give this one a miss.

title: Route 777
overview:
Route 777
    
        Play Route 777 demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: This pseudo-Hell’s Angels based slot is a high octane road trip down a four lane blacktop. The low volatility might call for a pit stop but there are other things to like.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Route 777 reimagines the hardcore biker road trip in line with a 777-slot. The game features a motorcycle gang patch and a desert background that can’t help but conjure up the idea of both Route 66 and the Hell’s Angels disaster at Altamont.
The reels are overlaid with a series of rotating animations of scorpions, dried cattle bones, and worn out cars dumped on the side of the road.
If you enjoy the open road, this slot is doing its best to create a high-octane version of the classic road trip adventure.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are a definite selling point for this slot. From the motes of dust that dance in the beams of the desert sunset background, to the orange-monochrome animated loops that frame the reels. The symbols are neat and simple, the gang patch is suitably threatening, and the standard fruit and bells are augmented with the fruit of a prickly pear cactus.
The slot is accompanied by a rock and roll soundtrack that echoes the feel of movies like Easy Rider. It all blends well with the jazzed up animations, and the win & spin sounds.
Overall, the visual presentation of the slot is fantastic.

media.caption: Win in the Route 777 slot

Gameplay.text:
Route 777 is played on a three by three reel with seventeen win lines.
The gameplay is pretty straightforward with a few simple twists, mostly relating to respins and a pair of bonuses (details below).
When the first two reels land with an identical set of symbols, the player is awarded with five respins. The first two reels move down by one symbol between each respin.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols.
Hitting three Wilds on one spin triggers the Free Spin Bonus. The player gets a randomised number of free spins between five and fifteen.
Hitting three Wilds in one spin during the free spins trigger the Fortune Wheel Bonus. During this bonus, the wheel spins until the player either collects three identical sevens or the stop sign lands. If the player gets three identical sevens, the player is awarded the payout associated with the seven in question. Rarer sevens pay out more.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.3%, a little over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is low, which makes it a poor match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Full paytable of the Route 777 slot machine

Conclusion.text:
The low volatility of this slot turns us off a bit, but the decent RTP and excellent gameplay make it a good slot for the right kind of player. If you’re not too worried about the low variance play and have always dreamed of riding a chopped hog with the Hell’s Angels, this could be a good slot for you.
Otherwise you may want to give this one a skip and seek out something similar in the realm of minimalist slots.

title: Wild Toro
overview:
Wild Toro
    
        Play Wild Toro demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Pit your wits against a raging bull in this slot with high volatility and an RTP of 96.3%, you’ll want to charge into this game like a bull at a red rag.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Wild Toro is based around the world of bullfighting. It sidesteps the less savoury aspects of the sport, by rendering the whole thing as a Tom and Jerry style contest between a cartoon bull and a rakish matador.
The other symbols lean into this with old style Spanish coins, ladies fans, and roses.
The tone of the tale (or tail) is charming and upbeat and combines well with the clever gameplay gimmicks that are built in.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
With its cartoon symbols rendered beautifully and its highly mobile animated win, spin, and walking Wild sequences, Wild Toro is a lovely slot to look at. The symbols are rendered with plenty of character and the style stands out against other, similar themed slots.
The music track is limited to wins, and the range of sound effects is a bit generic for a slot that is otherwise rich in character. There are ambient crowd noises which lend the game some atmosphere, but the win and spin sounds could be from any slot of any kind.
Overall, though, this slot is an example of excellent design.

media.caption: Win in the Wild Toro slot

Gameplay.text:
Wild Toro is a five reel slot with four rows.
The game uses an unusual "connecting ways" system to determine winning combinations. This means that combinations must start in reel one and move to adjacent reels. Unlike an "any way" winning system the symbols in a winning combo must be adjacent or touch diagonally. On a five by four slot this makes for 178 win ways.
There is a bonus game, but no gamble feature.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Toro and Matador symbols.
The Toro symbol is a special Wild. On a typical spin it works like any other Wild. However, if there is also a Matador symbol on the reel, the Matador will trigger a free respin. After every respin the Toro will move one space, leaving a Wild Symbol each time.
When the Toro lands on a Matador, the Matador is removed from the reels. When there are no more Matadors, the respins end and the player is paid.
The rules for Toro’s movements are always one space towards any Matador on its reel. If there is no Matador on its reel, it will either move left or right one space. If it has not been to reel five, it will then opt for one space to the right. If it is on reel five or has been to reel five at some point, then it moves one space to the left.

media.caption: A combination of 3 Matadors triggers free respins

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.3%, this is a little over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is high, which makes it a good match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Full paytable of the Wild Toro slot machine

Conclusion.text:
High volatility and a moderately high RTP make this slot appealing as a strategic choice.
The slot also gains points for having a lot of personality and atmosphere. The theme is cleverly executed and works at every stage from the visuals to the bonus games.
Overall, we recommend this slot.

title: Taco Brothers
overview:
Taco Brothers
    
        Play Taco Brothers demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Mexico, 1881 only you and the three Taco brothers can save Santa Maria from Captain Diaz and make a few pesos doing it. Jump aboard this burro for some great slot fun.

Theme and Storyline.text:
The story, as laid out in Taco Brothers’ opening animation, is this: in 1881 the utopian Mexican town of Santa Maria enjoys free tacos for all until Captan Diaz took over the city. In response three brave brothers rose up. Now Paso, Pepe and Pico fight for "freedom and for tacos".
A noble cause if there ever was one.

media.alt: Taco Brothers has great visual design
media.caption: Taco Brothers slot machine has great visual design

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
This blatantly silly set up is supported by fantastic, cartoonish art of the three brothers, as well as plenty of other stereotypical Mexicana: tequila bottles, mariachi guitars, and wild west safes.
The animations for this art are slick and varied with all the little flourishes that make a top tier slot feel that much classier than the average. Little things like fading out of non-winning symbols and side animations of gold falling into the player’s bankroll bar all add to the experience.
Even the soundtrack has been created with maximal class and if you don’t like it they put the mute button up before you even open the game.

media.alt: Non-winning symbols fade out in Taco Brothers
media.caption: Non-winning symbols fade out after the spin for better visual contrast

Gameplay.text:
Taco Brothers is a 243 ways, five reel slot.
The gameplay is simple with just the bonus features listed below to break it up. But the slot is of such high-quality that it is a delight to play just for that reason.
The game also comes with a betting strategy button, that automatically changes your bet according to the chosen system (for example the leveller increases the bet after every five consecutive losses). Although none of the strategies works well with our recommendations, it's an interesting innovation that definitely adds to the game.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
Taco Brothers has three special symbols. The Wild, Taco Wild and Bonus symbols.
The Wild symbol plays as any symbol other than the Taco Wild and Bonus symbols allowing you to rack up wins.
The Taco Wild allows a respin for a third Bonus symbol when two fall.
The bonus symbol itself triggers The Wild Escape bonus game. In this game one by one each brother is dropped onto reel 5 as a "Running Wild" which moves to the left each subsequent spin and otherwise plays like a normal Wild. The game comes to an end when all three brothers make it all the way across (15 spins in a normal run) or end up in jail (see below).
Two further symbols are part of this game: Captain Diaz – who when he lands locks the Running Wild in place and deactivates its ability to play as a wild – and Senorita – who resets the spins sending any of the three brothers that isn't locked to the start, sets free any locked wild and therefore adding many extra free spins.

This slot has a classic fruit machine theme.

Overall, the style is minimalistic, from the aesthetics to the gameplay. Players won’t find surprises here, but may like the familiar mood relaxing.

media.caption: Win in the Burning Wins: Classic 5 Lines slot machine

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The animation of each fruit is realistic and mouthwatering. Beads of condensation glint on the various lemons, oranges, cherries, and grapes. This lends them an especially fresh and appealing look.
This fruit animation style goes above and beyond the colourful motifs of some games. Clearly, extra care was taken to make each piece of fruit a tasty piece of art.
The game design is otherwise quite minimalistic, with an unobtrusive dark purple background and understated reel framing.
There is no background music for this game, but rather a satisfying clicking upon spins as the reels fall into place. This adds to the feeling that players are using an old-fashioned piece of real life machinery.
Wins prompt a cheery series of shimmering chimes. This hits the right mark between festive and yet still not shrill. Most players will be happy to leave the sounds on and enjoy the atmosphere they add.

Gameplay.text:
Burning Wins is a three reel, three row slot, with five win lines.
Gameplay is very classic, with a pleasant pace.

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:

We do not recommend this high RTP, medium volatility fruit-themed slot.

This slot does not bring anything particularly original to the table, and without a better set of mathematical stats, it’s simply not worth most players’ time.
The lack of bonus opportunities makes the gameplay a less exciting venture. Some players might like the soothing simplicity, but many will be craving variety.

title: Fluffy Favourites
overview:
Fluffy Favourites
    
        Play Fluffy Favourites demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Lazily designed and expensive to play, we would prefer if Fluffy Favourites stayed in the claw machine.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Fluffy Favourites has a somewhat split personality. In the background is a big top tent and a wide-open field. On the reels are a batch of soft toys and the occasional claw out of a shopping mall grabber machine. The connection between these two images is, presumably, that sometimes you find such machines at the circus and at fairs.
The heart of the machine is the stuffed toys rather than the setting. These adorable fluffy favourites of the title are rendered in a children's story art style that makes them hard not to love.

media.caption: Win in the base game

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are similarly two toned. On the one hand is the crude digital drawing of the background and on the other are the painstakingly drawn watercolour toys on the reels.
The rest of the game has a kind of primary colour, kindergarten feel to it. The animations are simple blinking lines to show wins and the spinning of the reels.
The action has no musical accompaniment except for some drums while the reel spins and the win and spin sounds are standard audio calqued from other slots in Eyecon’s line up.

media.caption: Player can change betting options of number of winlines together with the usual betting options

Gameplay.text:
Fluffy Favourites consists of a five reel slot with three rows and twenty five win lines.
The game has a picking bonus and a free spin bonus, as well as a gamble feature that allows you to play double or nothing with your winnings. The gamble feature does not always appear in the game.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol. Three or more Wilds anywhere on the reels will trigger the Free Spin bonus.
The Free Spin bonus starts with five free spins per Wild in the triggering spin. A multiplier of three is applied to all winnings during the Free Spin bonus.
Hitting three or more of the Scatter symbol triggers a picking game in which the player is awarded one pick per symbol on the triggering spin. The player picks items, each of which has a randomly assigned multiplier on it. The winnings are then calculated as the player's bet on the triggering spin times the multiplier.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 95.30%, comfortably coming in at below average (our yardstick for average is roughly 96%).
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.01 if you play just one line, up to a maximum of $/£/€15.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a very weak match for our preferred slot machine strategies.

media.caption: Full paytable for the Fluffy Favourites slot

Conclusion.text:
Fluffy Favourites is not a very engaging slot. The artwork is slapdash and inconsistent, the sound effects dull and jarring, and the gameplay plain and uninteresting.
However, the biggest turn off for us is the low return to player. At 0.7 percentage points under the approximate average return to player, Fluffy Favourites is far from being one of our favourites, or even getting a recommendation.

title: Irish Luck
overview:
Irish Luck
    
        Play Irish Luck demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: With a very low RTP (95%) you’ll need more than Irish Luck to have fun at this slot.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Leaning heavily on vaguely problematic stereotypes about Guiness and leprechauns, Irish Luck is an Ireland-themed slot that focuses on the myths and legends of the islands.
Four-leaf clovers abound along with rainbows and fairy folk who haunt the remnants of ruined castles on the reel.
It’s a bright, light, and colourful setting. But one which feels very derivative and somewhat overdone.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are a little bit kitsch. The artwork feels like it was pulled from an illustrated storybook published in the 90s and the background is a rather bland looking child’s drawing of a landscape with a rainbow.
The animations are simple and the sound effects even simpler.
There is no background music, and no spin sounds. There are a few sound effects when a bonus symbol lands or a win occurs, but on the whole the slot lacks the atmosphere that even a basic soundtrack would lend it.

media.caption: Win in the Irish Luck slot

Gameplay.text:
Irish Luck is played on a five reel grid with three rows. There are twenty-five win lines and a double or nothing gamble feature, which can be played at the end of any winning spin.
This is all pretty basic, but solid stuff. It won’t enchant players who are looking for something exotic. But if you like the basic slot format, this won’t disappoint.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Leprechaun Scatter and the Fairy Scatter symbols.
There are two Bonus Games.
Three or more Leprechaun Scatter symbols trigger a picking game. Players receive one pick for each Scatter they trigger the bonus with. Each pick reveals either a fairy or a leprechaun.
Fairies award a multiple of the player’s bet. Leprechaun’s award ten free spins. During any free spins the player wins, the payouts are doubled as compared to the base game.
Landing three or more Fairy Scatters trigger another picking game. In this one, the player is presented with clover leaves. Each leaf has a symbol under it. The player turns over clover leaves until they make a matching pair of symbols. The player then receives a payout that is linked to the symbol they match.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 95.0%, which means players are decidedly short on luck for this game. Our yardstick for average is roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.01 up to a maximum of $/£/€15.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is high, which would make it a great match for our preferred slot machine strategies if the RPT were higher. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Full paytable of the Irish Luck slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Irish Luck is a bit of a lame duck. It’s graphics feel cheap and derivative. No effort has been made in the animation or sound departments.
Nor have the team behind the scenes done a thing to make the game appeal. We like the high volatility, but it is paired with such a terrible RTP that it makes no difference.
The real luck of the Irish would prevent you from ever having to play this slot.

title: Demi Gods II
overview:
Demi Gods II
    
        Play Demi Gods II demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Demi Gods II is a great looking slot, with a ton of features and a beautifully realised world to play in. Look no further… unless the RTP of 95% or the low-ish volatility puts you off (which it should, by our standards).

Theme and Storyline.text:
Demi Gods II is one of many slots based around Ancient Greek mythology. Contrary to the title, almost all of the characters who appear in the game are full gods rather than demi-gods, but that doesn’t detract from the fun setting.
The base game is set in a cloudy sky and all the bonus levels take place in more exotic locales ranging from the depths of Hades to Mount Olympus. On the rosters are Zeus and Ares, along with a few other gods, and even the Wild symbols depict the winged sandals of Hermes.
It’s a great setting fabulously realised.

media.caption: Example of simple win in Demi Gods II slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
That realisation is done through a really extraordinary visual style. The Ace to Nine symbols do much of the work on the screen but the big winners are the so-called "High Symbols". Each of these High Symbols comes stacked on the reels. The stacking is done in such a way that it allows the artists to do full-length portraits that run across the full length of each High Symbol.
The effect is nice to look at and a fancy twist on the typical arrangement of such things.
On top of this, there is a panoply of animations. Reels catch fire while they spin after a Free Spin symbol falls, graphics fall in 3D from above the screen, and even the backgrounds are given full parallax animations.
The music is ambient drums that are background enough to not get on one’s nerves when they loop around incessantly and every possible opportunity has been taken to add some flavour to the sounds made by the symbols and even the different characters.
They really went all out on the design for this one.

media.caption: All Gods from Demi Gods II slot game are stacked on reels

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay is varied and fast-paced. With fifty winlines across five reels and the constant chance of random interventions (like the multiplier symbols), there is always something to look at and look forward to.
There are several bonuses (see below for details) which all add to the experience.
Overall this is a slot with high quality gameplay and lots of it.

media.alt: Demi Gods II Map of bonuses
media.caption: Map displaying all bonus rounds in Demi Gods II slot
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The key bonus feature in Demi Gods II is the Free Spin Journey Feature. This is triggered if you hit three or more Free Spin symbols.
There are four stages to the Free Spin Journey Feature, and each time you trigger it you move on to the next stage.
The first is Hades where every time you win, a respin occurs moving all the symbols one reel to the right and spinning up a new first reel. This can be retriggered if it results in another win.
The second stage is Aphrodite’s Bower where you get 5 free spins. On the first spin, the whole first reel is wild, on the second spin, the wild reel moves to reel two and so on until the final reel.
Ares’ fortress is where you go when you trigger the free spins for the third time. In this feature, all wilds expand to fill the reel they land on.
In the fourth and final stage, Zeus will grant you 4-7 Wild symbols every spin. On top of this, all the High Symbols are removed making the odds of winning higher (although lowering the average size of your win per line when you do).
There are also Win Multipliers that can give you a multiplier that applies to any winnings that you have won on that spin.
The game has a standard Wild symbol which plays as any symbol except the Win Multipliers and Free spin symbols. Get five in a row and they pay out 150 times your bet per spin.

media.alt: Demi Gods II Hades bonus round
media.caption: Respin feature occurs in Hades' free spins bonus rounds

media.alt: Demi Gods II Aphrodite bonus round
media.caption: Aphrodite's free spins bonus round

media.alt: Demi Gods II Ares bonus round
media.caption: Ares' Free spins bonus game
Multiplier bonus appears at random

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
Given how luxurious a slot this is, it is rather a shame to find out its rather stingy -- with a vig of 5% the return to player is just 95%, well below the yardstick we use of 96% as an industry average.
Due to being a fixed 50 winline slot, the minimum bet on the site we tested was €/£/$0.50 per spin and the maximum a huge €/£/$500 per spin.
The game is medium to low variance, which means you’ll be winning a lot of the time, but only relatively small amounts when you do.

media.caption: Contrary to the low variance of the Demi Gods II slot an epic win boosts your balance nicely

Conclusion.text:
The game is so beautifully designed it is a pity not to recommend it more enthusiastically, but for us, the vig is just too high.
But if you are not particularly fussed by this there are worse slots to spend your time on.

title: Panda King
overview:
Panda King
    
        Play Panda King demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Although we all love pandas, we do not love Panda King. This dull slot fails to charm at a superficial level and below the surface offers a poor RTP and insufficient volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Panda King is themed around the adorable black and white bears of East Asia, with their bamboo forest habitat providing a backdrop for a range of Sinocentric odds and ends. The style of the slot feels like it had more in common with a London Chinese takeaway menu than the real culture of China and does look a little tacky at first glance.
But the pandas are cute and the lotus blossoms, pagodas and decorative waterfalls are all quite prettily rendered, so, in the end, the theme kind of works in this Ainsworth's offering.

media.caption: Visuals are nice and clean

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are pretty well drawn, with easily identifiable symbols rendered in high-def.
These symbols are animated smoothly with good backing sound effects, but no music. This might be a blessing given how bad many slot soundtracks are, but a good soundtrack could have really added to the mood on this one.

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay is rather bland with no gamble feature, no minigames, and only free spins as a bonus. The main game is a twenty win line slot played on five reels. Though the game does allow you to chose how many winlines you ultimately play.
Little effort has been made to make the game engaging beyond this.

media.caption: Winlines are clearly defined in Panda King slot machine
Gameplay video featuring 8 free spins bonus game

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There are three special symbols.
There is the Panda symbol which plays as a Wild (or as the game calls it a "Substitute") symbol and can stand in for any symbol except the Scatter symbol.
The Scatter symbol is the second special symbol. When three or more Scatter symbols fall, regardless of where they land on the reels, the game also triggers the free spin bonus.
The Yin Yang Scatter triggers free spins. You can then choose from three options – eight, ten, or twelve free spins with a different set of symbols all converted to Wilds. The more spins, the fewer Panda symbols total on the reels for those spins.
For example, if you chose eight free spins then for those eight spins all of the "waterfall", "coin", "pergola", "lotus" and "ingot" symbols will be replaced by the Panda symbol. If you choose twelve free spins then only the first three will be replaced by Pandas.
Last special symbol is the Fortune symbol, which appears only in free spins. The Fortune symbol is stacked on all 5 reels and pays on any positions, up to 5 symbol hits. Also, whenever you hit at least 5 Fortune symbols together with at least 3 Wilds your winnings are then multiplied.

media.caption: Top symbols paytable in the base game

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player on this slot machine is a very low 94.34%. This is a deal breaker for us, anything under 96% we tend to avoid.
The minimum bet per spin on the site we tested was €/£/$0.20 and the maximum bet per spin was €/£/$100.00.
The slot has medium volatility. This does not play well with our strategies which largely focus on high-volatility slots.

media.caption: Special feature's paytable in Panda King slot

Conclusion.text: Panda King would probably not get a recommendation even if its RTP were not so low. It’s volatility isn’t high enough, the gameplay is weak and the visual and design elements are weak.

title: Eagle Bucks
overview:
Eagle Bucks
    
        Play Eagle Bucks demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Eagle Bucks is yet another nature themed slot that does nothing new or imaginative and charges you an insanely high vig for the displeasure of playing it. Give this one a miss.

Theme and Storyline.text:
America – that land of landscapes, where the buffalo roam and eagles soar – is the subject taken as Eagle Bucks’ theme. The setting is that of a Rocky Mountain pine forest, the symbols are deer, cougars, eagles and wolves. The title suggests the increasingly unpopular idea of hunting these creatures but apart from the title no hint of that pastime remains.
Instead, you can hop into a relaxing wilderness trail and spot the wildlife as you try to make your way to some kind of lucky strike.

media.caption: Example of simple win in Eagle Bucks slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are perfectly fine. They are higher definition that many similarly styled slots and more care has been put into ensuring that the symbols don’t look too tacky.
That said the visuals show little imagination, and in the case of the animations, none. The whole style for the slot is very basic.
The sound is entirely recorded in short stings, and when you win a few things on a single spin the effect can be like switching radio stations rapidly as there is no unity of tone between the various sound effects and brief musical clips.

Gameplay.text:
Gameplay is extremely bland with almost no variation to the usual push button style of play. There are no additional features to change the pace, no gamble feature, and just a simple bonus feature (see below for details).
What you get is a twenty win line, five reel slot with low volatility and very little fun.

media.caption: Gameplay video featuring 10 free spins with additional 5 spins

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There is a Wild symbol with the face of a bald eagle on it. This symbol plays as any other symbol except the Scatter. If you get a line of them on a win line they are also the highest paying symbol to make your standard wins with.
The Scatter symbol pays out if you hit three or more anywhere on any of the reels.
Hit three Scatter symbols or more and you also trigger ten free spins. Sometimes these spins will be awarded with reel five being entire locked in as Wild symbols.

media.caption: Visuals in Eagle Bucks are nice and clear

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
During free spins there are no eagle symbols on reel one, but on all other reels whenever you hit an eagle the eagle expands to fill that reel. You can retrigger another five free spins if you hit three or more Scatter symbols again during the free spins.
The site we tested allowed a spread of bets ranging from £/$/€0.01 per spin, if you played just a single line, all the way up to £/$/€200.00 per spin playing with the largest bet per line on all twenty win lines.
This is a very wide ranging bet spread, but unfortunately, the return to player is only 94.09%, almost two full percentage points below our yardstick return to player of 96%.
The volatility of this game is also low. We normally prefer high volatility games because they work best with our strategies.

media.caption: Eagle Bucks slot - top symbols paytable

Conclusion.text:
Eagle Bucks is a bog-standard slot machine with a boring theme and no innovations to keep us excited.
When you add this basicness to the low return to player and low volatility we have to suggest you look elsewhere for your slot based fun.

title: Dragon Lines
overview:
Dragon Lines
    
        Play Dragon Lines demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Dragon Lines is a pretty slot machine to look at themed around Chinese dragons, but with no sound design, simple gameplay, a low RTP, medium volatility and a somewhat lame bonus feature we do not recommend this slot.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Dragon Lines is Ainsworth’s slot that uses the theme of Chinese dragons, drawing out a line of symbols that range from regular old dragons to fireworks, hats and dragon themed Yin-Yang symbols.
The rich red and gold of the theme is nice enough and the slot comes with several other thematic threads in its design aimed at drawing you in.

media.caption: Dragon Lines symbols are nice and shiny

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Unfortunately, not all these threads are well realised.
Where it does shine in the design department is the visuals. The symbols are lively and classy. The dragon symbol comes to life with a fun animation when it is part of a win and overall the art style works together to generate an atmosphere.
The sound, on the other hand, is very poor. There is no background music or sound effects, instead, you get a simple set of reel noises and a brief little noise when you win. Sound can draw you in and elevate a simple slot experience but this slot makes no effort in that direction.

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay is pretty simple. The main quirk is that there are one hundred win lines – a very high number on a slot like this – spread in patterns over five reels.
The rest of the gameplay is rather lacking. There is no gamble feature, no minigames, and only the most basic of bonuses.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Scatter symbol serves as a trigger for the bonus Free Spins. You need to hit three or more. In addition, three will win two times your bet per spin while hitting five will win you one hundred times your bet per spin.
The Free Spins bonus provides you with ten free spins. You can retrigger five more free spins by hitting three or more Scatter symbols again during the Free Spins.
There is a Wild symbol that plays as any other symbol except the Scatter symbol and will also pay out if you hit a winline in the same manner as a regular symbol.
Wilds only appear on reels three to five, except during the free spins, when they are bumped over to the left by one and appear only on reels two to four.

media.caption: Dragon Lines slot has expanding Wild symbol

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player on this game is 94.30%, like a lot of Ainsworth slots, this is substantially below the 96% yardstick that we use. This counts heavily against this slot.
While the software allows for a maximum bet of up to £/$/€10,000 per spin, the site we tested capped the bet at £/$/€5.00 per winline for a maximum of £/$/€500 per spin. The minimum bet is £/$/€0.01 per line.
The slot has medium volatility. We would prefer if it were higher.

media.caption: Low symbols paytable in Dragon Lines slot
High symbols paytable in Dragon Lines slot

Conclusion.text: Dragon Lines is visually satisfying but falls a little short in almost every other measure. It is by no means a terrible slot, but it is mediocre and an easy slot for us to turn down for a recommendation.

title: Football Fever
overview:
Football Fever
    
        Play Football Fever demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: This soccer-themed slot gets an instant red card for its poor RTP (92.3%) and mediocre execution.

Theme and Style.text:
Football Fever is a soccer-themed slot game from Genii.
The game attempts to recreate the thrill of an international football match, combining the stadium setting and cheering crowds with classic soccer-themed imagery. The classic black and white ball, referee whistles, and yellow cards are integrated into the visuals, soundtrack, and gameplay respectively.
This slot will appeal to soccer fans and anyone who has longed for a season ticket to see their favorite team play on their home field.

media.caption: Genii's Football Fever slot win

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics of Football Fever are fairly basic. The symbols on the reels have the look of rotoscoped art and the animations for a win simply rotate elements of the image and flash words up.
The soundtrack is a short somewhat bothersome clip of stadium music backed by a much less bothersome roar of football fans cheering a match. The sound effects are what you would expect from a slot like this, they are pretty generic with a handful of football-themed noises (like the referee’s whistle) thrown in.
All in all, it's nothing fancy, but the front end of this slot does its job reasonably well.

Gameplay.text:
Football Fever has three rows and five reels, which combined with the any-way wins system means there are 243 ways to win.
Wins are formed by matching symbols anywhere on consecutive reels starting from the left.
The publisher Genii does not appear to have made certain key statistics available for this slot. Among the missing details is the maximum win for the player. Not providing this information is a red flag that players would be well advised to view cautiously.

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol in this game comes with a classic black-and-white soccer ball image. This Wild substitutes for every other symbol, except for the Scatter (with a yellow card image on it), and the Free Spin symbol (with the referee’s whistle on it).
The Free Spin symbol pays out as a scatter for two or more symbols anywhere on the reels. If the player lands three or more Free Spin symbols, then the Free Spin bonus is triggered as follows:
During the Free Spins Bonus, all wins are tripled, and both the Free Spin Bonus and Bonus Penalty round can be triggered or retriggered during the Free Spin Bonus game.
Three or more Scatter symbols trigger the Bonus Penalty Round. This is a free spin bonus. However, it does not include the triple score multiplier.

media.caption: Paytable for Football Fever slot from Genii

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of Football Fever is 92.3%. This is among the worst RTPs we have come across. We use a yardstick for an average of roughly 96%. This slot comes in way below this average. This alone would be enough for us to suggest you avoid this slot.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.25 up to a maximum of $/£/€31.25 per spin.
Genii has not provided details of this slot’s volatility. The size of the payouts would suggest relatively high volatility, but without confirmation, we cannot recommend this slot.

Conclusion.text:
This slot is probably one you can skip. The design and theme are pretty mediocre, the soundtrack functional at best and annoying at worst, and the RTP is miserably low (92.3%).
When you add in the limited information about the volatility and maximum wins, it becomes clear that this soccer-themed slot is one to avoid.

title: Joan of Arc
overview:
Joan of Arc
    
        Play Joan of Arc demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: A nice looking medieval slot machine based around a heroic figure from French history should be an easy sell, but with no published RTP, medium variance and limited features, Joan of Arc fails to deliver.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Now the flames they followed Joan of Arc
As she came riding through the dark;
No moon to keep her armour bright,
No man to get her through this very smoky night.
She said, ‘I'm tired of the war,
I want the kind of work I had before.’ – Joan of Arc, by Leonard Cohen.
She may not have the kind of work she had before, or indeed the kind of work she had after her death when she was canonised as a Saint of the Catholic Church. Where she once served as a military advisor and leader to the French during the Hundred Years War now, in GameArt’s Joan of Arc slot machine, she is representing the treasury.
You’ll need to land her symbol if you want the biggest rewards the game has to offer.

media.alt: Joan of Arc wild symbol win
media.caption: Winning combination with Wild symbol

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The medieval setting is rendered pleasantly with a field of battle in the background and chainmail backgrounds on some of the symbols. The artwork is well rendered and coupled with solid reel and win animations to make the whole thing visually appealing.
The music too is pitched just right, setting the mood and in keeping with the theme, but not so invasive as to become annoying as it loops around and around.

Gameplay.text:
Despite being a five reel slot with 243 winlines the gameplay is relatively slow, with wins coming in fairly rarely. The real excitement comes along during the bonus rounds which are described in greater detail below.
There is a gamble feature if you want to raise your volatility and add in a little variation to your game as well.

media.alt: Joan of Arc - 3 Scatter hits with free spins
media.caption: Hitting 3 Scatter symbols awards 10 free spins
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There are two main bonus features. The first is triggered by the Scatter symbol when you hit three or more in a go. As well as receiving a payout for hitting the Scatter symbol you also receive ten free spins.
The second bonus feature involves the ‘Arrow Border’ symbols. These are like the regular symbols but have a changed background and border. When these Arrow Symbols are part of a winning combination they then expand to fill the reel they are in. The expansion splits each symbol so that for the purpose of counting winning combos the original symbol remains in play with the expanded symbol next to it (see image below).
During the free spins, any Arrow Border symbol expands regardless of whether it is part of a winning combo.
The game also has a Wild symbol which plays as any symbol except for the Scatter symbol.

media.alt: Joan of Arc - Expanding symbol win
media.caption: Arrow border symbols can expand in order to raise your winnings

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
With its RTP unpublished, it is hard to decide if this game is worth your time or not on the basis of the vig. Caution would dictate avoiding any slot that is unwilling to publish its basic statistics like this.
The game has medium volatility, which doesn’t lend itself very well to our preferred strategies.
On the site, we tested the minimum bet was €/£/$0.30 per spin and the maximum was €/£/$150.00 per spin. This should cover all but the smallest of bankrolls.

media.caption: Joan of Arc slot offers a gamble function (if you turn it on)
Joan of Arc - full paytable

Conclusion.text:
Although visually pleasant and well made, Joan of Arc suffers from two major setbacks.
The first main problem is that it has poor or absent statistics: the RTP is unpublished and the variance is very middle of the road.
The second is that the gameplay is somewhat uninspired, with only the most basic features to back the visuals up.
We do not recommend this game.

overview:

about_game: Haunted house and rock’n’roll, taking the best of a death metal sensibility House of Doom is great fun. It works well with our high variance strategies and has an RTP of 96.11%. Enter the house of doom at your peril!

Theme and Storyline.text:
House of Doom appears to be half a haunted house themed slot, half death metal album cover borrowed from Candlemass’ 2018 album of the same name. As such it has a decidedly cool series of images to work with, the looming Amityville churchyard full of skulls in the background, the roses and pentacles and of course the blaring electric guitars on the soundtrack.
It is a really original tone in a market saturated by the broadest of geographical (under the sea for example) and historical themes (goldrush, Egypt, Vikings…). Let’s rock!

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
As suggested above the highly original theme is brought to life with a pleasing array of artistic choices.
The music is the most obvious one with its dirty guitar riffs and organ backing tracks. This goes well with the album cover style of the art which makes for some gorgeous and sinister symbols on all the reels.
This is all topped off with high-quality animation which is never overblown but adds a little visual variety to each shift of the game from spin to win.

media.alt: House of Doom - Free spins win

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay is fairly basic. The main game is a simple five reel slot with ten winlines and a basic bonus game of free spins along with a point and click Skulls of the Abyss bonus game.
There is no gamble feature or other mini-games to speak of, so you need to be sure you enjoy the main game if you are in it for the long haul.
